00168 template <class BPQNode>
00169 inline void GBPQueue2<BPQNode>::setUp(int a, int b, int a2, int b2)
00170 { 
00171   assert(b >= a);
00172 
00173   _T = new GBPQueue<BPQNode>[b - a + 2];  
00174   _offset = a - 1;
00175   _high = b - a + 1;
00176   _max = 0;
00177 
00178   for (unsigned int i=0; i<=_high; i++) {
00179     _T[i].setUp(a2, b2);
00180   }
00181 
00182   _T[0].makeDummy(); // sentinel
00183 
00184   /* The propose of_T[0] is to reduce the boundary check. _T[0] acts
00185      like a non-empty list so that _T[0].isEmpty() always returns
00186      false. Don't insert items to _T[0]. */
00187 }

00260 template <class BPQNode>
00261 inline BPQNode& GBPQueue2<BPQNode>::popFront()
00262 { 
00263   assert(_max>0);
00264   BPQNode& res = _T[_max].popFront();
00265   while (_T[_max].isEmpty()) _max--; 
00266   return res;
00267 
00268   /* Without the sentinel, the above while loop needs to check the
00269      boundary condition, i.e., max > 0:
00270            while (_max > 0 && _T[_max].isEmpty()) _max--; 
00271      Other functions below may also need the similar check.
00272    */
00273 }
